---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="Privacy Policy for TechPickr"
	pubDate={new Date('2025-01-01')}
>
	<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
	<p><strong>Last updated: January 1, 2025</strong></p>

	<p>
		TechPickr ("we", "us", or "our") operates the website techpickr-blog.pages.dev (the "Service").
		This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal
		data when you use our Service.
	</p>

	<h3>Information We Collect</h3>
	<p>
		We do not directly collect personal information from visitors. Our website may use third-party
		services that collect anonymized usage data to improve site performance.
	</p>

	<h3>Affiliate Links</h3>
	<p>
		TechPickr participates in the Amazon Associates affiliate program. When you click on affiliate
		links and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. Amazon may collect
		data according to their own privacy policy.
	</p>

	<h3>Pinterest Integration</h3>
	<p>
		We use the Pinterest API to automatically publish content (blog article previews and pins) to
		our Pinterest business account. No personal data of visitors is collected or transmitted through
		this integration. The Pinterest API is used solely to manage our own Pinterest content.
	</p>

	<h3>Cookies</h3>
	<p>
		We do not use cookies directly. Third-party services embedded on our site (e.g., Amazon, Pinterest)
		may use cookies according to their own policies.
	</p>

	<h3>Third-Party Links</h3>
	<p>
		Our website may contain links to external sites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices
		of those sites and encourage you to review their privacy policies.
	</p>

	<h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
	<p>
		We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with
		an updated revision date.
	</p>

	<h3>Contact</h3>
	<p>
		If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us via the information on our
		website.
	</p>
</Layout>
